> And Idea of mine for a story about Vampires and Detectives</span><hr size=1> Okay, I'm new here obviously...but I have posted before with another story. Well I have a new idea for a thriller story type dealio. Well it starts off with a detective, and his partner. The main character bein' a guy and the girl bein his partner. Well they investigate murders that are based on the ways Vlad the Impaler used to kill people. People are killed by bein' thrown on stakes and then bite marks on the neck, kinda like an insignia for the killer. Well they investigate the murders getting really hot on the murderers tail when the guy finally finds and confronts the murderer and the murder says &quot;Do you think i'm a vampire or another puny mortal? In order to find out..shoot me.&quot; Then i have a dillema..to make the guy shoot the murderer and then the story ends, so the reader can determine whether they thought it was a vampire or not..or to have the man shoot the murderer then jump to the next chapter, finally revealing what really happened, then i don't know where to make it a real vampire or a poser. Can anyone help me out here? <p><hr>
Beware of the ones you love can hurt you dearly.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/utaerx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TaerX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/19/02 5:57:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=721.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: And Idea of mine for a story about Vampires and Detectiv</span><hr size=1> Random thoughts:<br>
<br>
1) If you want the story to end, have the detective calmly aim, shoot, and have the vampire gasp in pain and collapse.  &quot;How....&quot; the vampire gasps before expiring.  The partner looks puzzled.  The detective merely shrugs and says, &quot;I took the precaution of handloading a few shells with Brazilian Ironwood.  If he reduces to dust, we'll know it was worth the effort.&quot;  From there, you can have the body reduce to dust or not, your choice.<br>
<br>
2) Fred Saberhagen wrote fiction about Sherlock Holmes and vampires.  I don't recall the exact book, but do recall it an enjoyable read.  <br>
<br>
3) One of the other Holmes/vampire novels I read (muddy recall) supposed that Holmes could have been a vampire himself.  Perhaps you can use that 'hook' and have the detective reveal himself to be a vampire, though one that tries hold on to his humanity.<br>
<br>
4) You may want to choose one or the other - Vlad the Impaler was a sadistic and cruel conquerer, bloodthirsty but not a neckbiter.  <br>
<br>
5) If you want the story to continue, you could have the detective shoot, the vampire shrug it off, laugh, and say, &quot;Now, I'll make you regret this for the rest of your days&quot;, and kill the detective's partner, leaving him traumatized.<br>
<br>
Please post what you decide to do, especially if it's not one of the above mad meanderings.  I'm very intrigued by the concept. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/udungeonklowne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DungeonKlowne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/19/02 4:57:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=721.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/silintknight/starwindchara.art WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: An Idea of mine for a story about Vampires and Detective</span><hr size=1> Ahh good ideas they are..very. TY i could work with them. I will stick with the Sadistic side to Vlad, for that is the side I enjoy more. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) But I could make the lead detective a vampire yes, and the criminal be the &quot;poser&quot; for say. But remember, I'm only 15 so I'm not too good with making puzzling situations, instead i have a large imagination. I have many other stories sitting up in my head. And I want this story to be a goods and puzzling one to have the reader guessing at every cliffhanger. And I'll take out the bitemarks. <p><hr>
Beware of the ones you love can hurt you dearly.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/utaerx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TaerX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/19/02 5:30:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=721.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: An Idea of mine for a story about Vampires and Detective</span><hr size=1> If you want a 'psycho horrror' aspect to it, you could make Vlad (who hails from the 1400's) and make him a vampire in a different sense.  Instead of merely sucking and living off blood, and being immortal based on vampirism, you could have him benefit by somehow extending his lifespan from inflicting pain and death (slowly) on others.  That would give a rationale for the over-the-top deaths.<br>
<br>
As for age, it doesn't matter much - on the net, no one knows your age unless you show it or tell it.  And if you're considering creating this sort of fiction at 15, you're further ahead than I was at that age - I was just rolling random monster encounters and amassing D&amp;D experience points. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uanimelibra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>animelibra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/21/02 9:45:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=721.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.mangatoanime.com/manga/avatars/Cowboy_Bebop_-_Ed_01.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re: an idea</span><hr size=1> What's wrong with D&amp;D??? I like the whole idea of a vampire finally getting some attention from the police; I don't see alot of Vampire reports in the newspaper these days. Its cool. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I'm with you on the whole &quot;I'm only [blank] ! What the hell can I do?&quot;  <p><hr>
"Some people say I must be a horrible person.  That's not true.  I have the heart of a young boy...on my desk." -Stephen King</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/utaerx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TaerX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/21/02 9:52:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=721.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re: an idea</span><hr size=1> Nothing's wrong with D&amp;D per se.  It's just that, after over a decade of gaming, I look back and see that most of the games I ran were basically collections of cliches and highlights from other films, books, anime, manga and any other media I encountered.<br>
<br>
I'm not dissing D&amp;D, nor D&amp;D players.  I'm just saying that when I was 15, I wasn't doing anything as creative as what the originator of this thread is proposing. <p><hr noshade size=1><center><font size=1><a href="http://www.freewebs.com/taerx/"> My FreeWebs Home Page</a> (Not a lot there)</font></center></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showPrevMessage?topicID=721.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showNextMessage?topicID=721.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=721.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.emailToFriend?topicID=721.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.threadControl?topicID=721.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=721.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=721.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub25.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="po